<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="57572" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">
Described with ocular spots (
<bibRefCitation author="Hartman, O." journalOrPublisher="University of Southern California Press, Los Angeles" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572" refId="B5999715" refString="Hartman, O., 1955. Essays in the Natural Sciences in Honor of Captain Allan Hancock on the occasion of his birthday July 26, 1955. University of Southern California Press, Los Angeles" title="Essays in the Natural Sciences in Honor of Captain Allan Hancock on the occasion of his birthday July 26, 1955." year="1955">Hartman 1955</bibRefCitation>
), but considered as absent in the re-description provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Blake, J. A" journalOrPublisher="Taxonomic atlas of the benthic fauna of the Santa Maria Basin and Western Santa Barbara Channel" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572" refId="B5999364" refString="Blake, J. A, 2000. . Taxonomic atlas of the benthic fauna of the Santa Maria Basin and Western Santa Barbara Channel 1" volume="1" year="2000">Blake (2000)</bibRefCitation>
. These spots are present in specimens from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Bahía">Bahia</normalizedToken>
de Chamela (Figs. 5D-E).
</paragraph>
